flowRoot.flowPara: This document contains in-application graphics for core gaffer apps. Exports are registered in the sidecar graphics.py file, which lists object IDs (as set in Object Properties -> ID) along with any associated size validation options.

All graphics must be aligned to pixel boundaries. It is reccomended to create an export boundary rect with the correct ID in the ExportAreas layer, then construct the artwork on the Artwork layer on top, within its bounds.
- Mouse cursors are registered in src/GafferUI/Pointer.cpp.
- The x,y coordinate of the pointer should be set to the coordinates of the pixel to be used when computing mouse/object intersection.
- All exports should use the 'pointer' prefix.
- Use integer pixel width lines where possible.
- Align 1px lines to 1/2 pixel gridlines to prevent anti-aliasing.
- Odd sized images are valid if its assists center alignment, especially at small scales.
- Use standard swatch fills/strokes where possible.
